data.title: The Diabetes Health Coach
data.subTitle: Healthy Eating e-Coaching Session: Reading nutrition facts labels

items.title: Getting Ready
items.text: How confident are you that you can read a Nutrition Facts label to help you with meal planning?

items.title: Step 1 - Get the Facts
items.text: Review the recommended e-Coaching Sessions and choose which you'd like to focus on first.

items.title: Step 2 - Practice
items.text: Now it's time to practice what you've learned.

items.title: Step 3 - Take Action

items.value: Tell a close friend about my depression and ask for support.
Join an online depression discussion forum.
Call a friend and invite them out this weekend.
Join an online social network on a topic that interests me.
Get a pet that likes to be cuddled, like a dog or cat.
Make a list of 3 friends and put it on my fridge.

items.text:
Are you ready to use what you've learned to make some healthy changes?
Choose 1 to 3 actions to try now.You're welcome to select more, but keep in mind that it's easier to stay focused on just a few actions at a time. Once you've mastered, you can come back and choose more

items.title: Step 4- Finish Up
items.text:
